                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320705-231-off1211 t18320705-231-crimeloc1213"></join>, and lost a silk handkerchief from my pocket - I was stooping at the time, and did not perceive it taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320705-231-person1930">
                  CHARLES 
                  PACKER
               <interp inst="t18320705-231-person1930" type="surname" value="PACKER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320705-231-person1930" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320705-231-person1930" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 26th of June I was standing at my father's door in Ball-alley; the prosecutor was stooping; I saw the prisoner, with another boy; the prisoner took the handkerchief from Mr. Liddell's pocket, put it into his bosom, and walked down the alley with the other boy - I told Liddell, and then went and asked the prisoner for it; he said he had not got it, but I saw it hanging out of his bosom, and took it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320705-231-person1931">
                  GEORGE 
                  DAVIS
               <interp inst="t18320705-231-person1931" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
